(Corrects spelling of governor’s name in second paragraph.)  The second-ranking member of the
 University of Virginia ’s board resigned today, the latest
development in the controversy surrounding the forced departure
of President Teresa Sullivan.  Mark Kington, vice rector of the university’s Board of
Visitors, stepped down today, according to a letter he sent to
Virginia Governor Robert McDonnell.  To contact the reporter on this story:
